Package ray.rage.common

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Disposable
    A disposable is an object that can be explicitly destroyed to release their internal resources.
    Factory<T>
    A factory is an object that's specifically meant to instantiate other objects of a specified type while minimizing coupling between the client and specific implementations.
    Manageable
    An manageable object is one whose setup and tear down is intended to be explicitly controlled to manage potentially expensive or sequence-sensitive operations with more predictability.
    Managed<T>
    A managed instance is one that is created by another object that's considered to be its "owner" and whose life-cycle is meant to be controlled by it.
    Nameable
    A nameable object is one that can be identified by a specific name.
    Visible
    A visible object is one that can be displayed in some way, such as an object in a scene.
